      • pool

        public static final SchedulablePoolThread.VdmThreadPoolExecutor pool
        Thread pool used by SchedulablePoolThread. It is a none blocking queue with an upper limit set to Integer.MAX_VALUE allowing it to freely expand. The thread pool will most likely make the Java VM throw OutOfMemoryError before Integer.MAX_VALUE is reached do the the native thread creation requiring 2 MB for each thread. "http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/ThreadPoolExecutor.html"
